{"type":"turn_end","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"We need to decide vote. Based on prior rounds: Mixed. As C1, we must look at record. The evidence shows NOTAM A1010/26 is airport closure, not FIR. The rule defines major closure as broad closure of commercial flights transiting, arriving, departing from Iranian airspace or major region, and limited exceptions do not disqualify. The question: does an airport operations NOTAM that closes all airports in western Tehran FIR and suspends permissions count as broad closure of commercial flights arriving/departing? It does restrict arrivals/departures at those airports, but maybe not transiting flights. However, the rule includes \"transiting, arriving in, and departing from Iranian airspace or a major region\". If airports closed, flights cannot depart/arrive at those airports, but could still overfly? Not prohibited. The record does not indicate overflight bans. So maybe not a \"major closure\" of the airspace region. The defense argument seems strong. Prior round votes are varied. As C1, we need to decide based on preponderance. I think the evidence does not clearly establish that Iran initiated a major closure of its airspace as defined. It shows airport closures, which may not meet the rule. So vote not_demonstrated.\n\nProvide concise rationale ≤3 sentences.\n\nNow call mcp with tool \"aar_submit_council_vote\" and args JSON string.\n\n","thinkingSignature":"reasoning"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"chatcmpl-tool-a71282a88d8ab9cf","name":"mcp","arguments":{"tool":"aar_submit_council_vote","args":"{\"vote\":\"not_demonstrated\",\"rationale\":\"The admitted NOTAM A1010/26 only closes airports in the western Tehran FIR and suspends permissions, without evidence of a broad airspace or transiting flight closure required by the market rule. The Q‑code indicates an aerodrome‑level notice, not a FIR closure, so the proposition’s definition of a major non‑weather closure is not satisfied. Accordingly, the preponderance of the record does not demonstrate the required closure.\"}"}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"openrouter","model":"openai/gpt-oss-120b","usage":{"input":19918,"output":420,"cacheRead":64,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":20402,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1781906958590,"responseId":"gen-1781906958-1fSrRBeMwwDI6kMMmPr1"},"toolResults":[{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"chatcmpl-tool-a71282a88d8ab9cf","toolName":"mcp","content":[{"type":"text","text":"ok: true\nmember_id: C1\ncase_id: arb-ex11a-20260619213136\nphase: deliberation\nopportunity_id: deliberation:2:C1\nremaining_ms: 892167\nattempts_remaining: 3\njson: {\"case_id\":\"arb-ex11a-20260619213136\",\"member_id\":\"C1\",\"ok\":true,\"result\":{\"text\":\"Council vote accepted.\"},\"turn\":{\"attempts_max\":3,\"attempts_remaining\":3,\"completed\":true,\"deadline\":\"2026-06-19T22:24:16.415257582Z\",\"deliberation_round\":2,\"member_id\":\"C1\",\"opportunity_id\":\"deliberation:2:C1\",\"phase\":\"deliberation\",\"remaining_ms\":892167,\"role_id\":\"council\",\"turn_number\":20}}"}],"details":{"mode":"call","mcpResult":{"content":[{"type":"text","text":"ok: true\nmember_id: C1\ncase_id: arb-ex11a-20260619213136\nphase: deliberation\nopportunity_id: deliberation:2:C1\nremaining_ms: 892167\nattempts_remaining: 3\njson: {\"case_id\":\"arb-ex11a-20260619213136\",\"member_id\":\"C1\",\"ok\":true,\"result\":{\"text\":\"Council vote accepted.\"},\"turn\":{\"attempts_max\":3,\"attempts_remaining\":3,\"completed\":true,\"deadline\":\"2026-06-19T22:24:16.415257582Z\",\"deliberation_round\":2,\"member_id\":\"C1\",\"opportunity_id\":\"deliberation:2:C1\",\"phase\":\"deliberation\",\"remaining_ms\":892167,\"role_id\":\"council\",\"turn_number\":20}}"}],"structuredContent":{"case_id":"arb-ex11a-20260619213136","member_id":"C1","ok":true,"result":{"text":"Council vote accepted."},"turn":{"attempts_max":3,"attempts_rema